p <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/simonqdy/sta553/main/data/w02-penguins.csv")
penguins <- mutate(p, body_mass = body_mass_g/3000)

library(png)
penguin_pic <- image_read("https://github.com/simonqdy/sta553/blob/main/image/penguin.png?raw=true")
#pp <- image_scale(penguin_pic,"50")

bill_length_mm = penguins$bill_length_mm
flipper_length_mm = penguins$flipper_length_mm
body_mass = penguins$body_mass
species = penguins$species
## identifying the ID
adelie.id = which(species=="Adelie") 
gentoo.id = which(species=="Gentoo")
chinstrap.id = which(species=="Chinstrap")
## color code
col.code =  c(alpha("orange",0.5),alpha("blue",0.5),alpha("red",0.5))

plot(bill_length_mm, flipper_length_mm, main = "flipper_length_mm vs bill_length_mm", type = "n")

## change the point size based on their boday_mass
points(bill_length_mm[adelie.id], flipper_length_mm[adelie.id], 
       pch = 19, col = col.code[1], cex = body_mass[adelie.id])
points(bill_length_mm[gentoo.id], flipper_length_mm[gentoo.id], 
       pch = 19, col = col.code[2], cex = body_mass[gentoo.id])
points(bill_length_mm[chinstrap.id], flipper_length_mm[chinstrap.id], 
       pch = 19, col = col.code[3], cex = body_mass[chinstrap.id])
legend("topleft", c("Adelie", "Gentoo", "Chinstrap"), 
                  col=col.code,
                  pch=c(19, 19, 19))

rasterImage(penguin_pic,55,184,60,203)

text(50, 173, "The point size is proportional to body_mass_g", col = "navy", cex = 1)
